Togetherly – Inner Circle Terms & Conditions
Last Updated: [DATE]

1. Eligibility
Inner Circle is a private, girls-only community within the Togetherly platform.
By joining, you confirm that you identify as a girl or woman and are legally eligible to use the platform.

2. Nature of the Community
Inner Circle is designed to provide a safer, more private space.
Content, interactions, and access are governed by stricter rules than the public areas of Togetherly.

3. Account Responsibility
You are responsible for all activity conducted through your account.
Sharing access, impersonation, or misuse of accounts is prohibited.

4. Community Conduct
You agree not to engage in harassment, hate speech, threats, sexual exploitation, or harmful behavior.
Any attempt to pressure, stalk, or intimidate another member is strictly prohibited.

5. Privacy & Confidentiality
Content shared within Inner Circle must not be copied, recorded, screenshotted, or shared outside the community.
Attempting to identify or contact members outside the app is not allowed.

6. Moderation & Enforcement
Togetherly reserves the right to moderate, remove content, suspend, or permanently ban users at its sole discretion.
Moderation decisions are final to protect community safety.

7. User-Generated Content
You retain ownership of content you create but grant Togetherly a non-exclusive license to host, display, and moderate such content for service operation and safety.

8. Messaging & Groups
Direct messages and group chats must follow all community rules.
Abusive or unsolicited messaging may result in immediate action.

9. Payments & Premium Features
Certain Inner Circle features may require payment.
All payments are subject to applicable app store terms.
Unless required by law, payments are non-refundable.

10. Security Expectations
You agree not to attempt to bypass safeguards, privacy protections, or moderation systems.

11. Termination
You may leave Inner Circle at any time via settings.
Togetherly may revoke access without notice for violations.

12. Disclaimer
Inner Circle is provided “as is.”
Togetherly does not guarantee uninterrupted access or user behavior.

13. Limitation of Liability
Togetherly shall not be liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from use of Inner Circle.

14. Governing Law
These terms are governed by the laws of India.
Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of courts in India.

15. Changes to Terms
Togetherly may update these terms at any time.
Continued use constitutes acceptance of updated terms.

